<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4635786>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Australophialus utinomii from Ranella gemmifera collected at Gonubie, female (A–B), D—cypris larva. A—Lateral view of whole specimen, right side; B—Burrow opening; C—Terminal cirri; D—Cypris larva, lateral view. Abbreviations: bo—burrow opening." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4635786/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4635788>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Australophialus utinomii from Burnupena cincta collected near East London. Scanning electron microscopy of general morphology and external features, female. A—comb collar; B—Magnified view of simple tooth at posterior margin of opercular bar; C—Terminal cirri (broken) protruding out of aperture; D—Opercular area, fronto-lateral view; E—Rostral area of opercular bar with spines and setae; F—Surface of lateral opercular area with multifid scales. Abbreviations: cc—comb collar, ob—opercular bar, tc—terminal cirri." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4635788/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

